<section role="topic" id="apns-setup-appid">
	<sectioninfo>
		<abstract>
			<para>Create an app ID the Apple Developer portal.</para>
		</abstract>
	</sectioninfo>
	<title id="apns-setup-appid.title">Step 1: Create an App ID</title>
	<para>Create an app ID to identify your app in the Apple Developer portal. You need this ID when
		you create an SSL certificate for sending push notifications, when you create an iOS
		distribution certificate, and when you create a provisioning profile.</para>
	<para>If you already have an ID assigned to your app, you can skip this step. You can use an
		existing app ID provided it doesn't contain a wildcard character ("*").
		<!--Need to verify this.--></para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To assign an App ID to your app</title>
		<step>
			<para>Sign in to your Apple Developer account at <ulink
					url="https://developer.apple.com/membercenter/index.action"
					>https://developer.apple.com/membercenter/index.action</ulink>.</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>Choose <guilabel>Certificates, Identifiers &amp; Profiles</guilabel>.</para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata
						fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/ios_appcert04.png"
						format="PNG" width="100%" scalefit="1" contentdepth="100%"/>
				</imageobject>
				<textobject>
					<phrase>Certificates, identifiers, and profiles.</phrase>
				</textobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>In the <guilabel>Identifiers</guilabel> section, choose <guilabel>App
					IDs</guilabel>.</para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata
						fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/ios_appcert05.png"
						format="PNG" width="100%" scalefit="1" contentdepth="100%"/>
				</imageobject>
				<textobject>
					<phrase>Identifiers section.</phrase>
				</textobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>In the <guilabel>iOS App IDs</guilabel> pane, choose the <guilabel>Add</guilabel>
				button (+).</para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata
						fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/ios_appcert06.png"
						format="PNG" width="100%" scalefit="1" contentdepth="100%"/>
				</imageobject>
				<textobject>
					<phrase>Add button.</phrase>
				</textobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>In the <guilabel>Registering an App ID</guilabel> pane, for <guilabel>Name</guilabel>, type
				a custom name for your app ID that makes it easy to recognize later.</para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata
						fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/ios_appcert07.png"
						format="PNG" width="100%" scalefit="1" contentdepth="100%"/>
				</imageobject>
				<textobject>
					<phrase>Registering an app ID.</phrase>
				</textobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>Choose the default selection for an App ID Prefix.</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>For <guilabel>App ID Suffix</guilabel>, select <guilabel>Explicit App ID</guilabel>, and
				type a bundle ID for your app. If you already have an app, use the bundle ID
				assigned to it. You can find this ID in the app project in Xcode on your Mac.
				Otherwise, take note of the bundle ID because you will assign it to your app in
				Xcode
				later.<!--This ID you enter should match the Bundle Identifier in your app's Info.plist. --></para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata
						fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/ios_appcert08.png"
						format="PNG" width="100%" scalefit="1" contentdepth="100%"/>
				</imageobject>
				<textobject>
					<phrase>App ID Suffix.</phrase>
				</textobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>Under <guilabel>App Services</guilabel> select <guilabel>Push
					Notifications</guilabel>.</para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata
						fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/ios_appcert09.png"
						format="PNG" width="100%" scalefit="1" contentdepth="100%"/>
				</imageobject>
				<textobject>
					<phrase>App services.</phrase>
				</textobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>Choose <guilabel>Continue</guilabel>. In the <guilabel>Confirm your App ID</guilabel> pane,
				check that all values were entered correctly. The identifier should match your app
				ID and bundle ID.</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>Choose <guilabel>Register</guilabel> to register the new app ID.</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>
